# Breadcrumb Consistency Rule

## Objective
Provide a single UX pattern for all page breadcrumbs so navigation remains predictable and maintainable.

## Requirements
1. All pages that display breadcrumb navigation **MUST** import and use the shared component
   ```typescript
   import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/common/Breadcrumbs';
   ```
2. Ad-hoc breadcrumb markup (manual `<nav>` with `>` separators) is **FORBIDDEN**.
3. The shared component consumes `ForumStructureContext` when a forum or zone slug is present and auto-builds
   Home → Zone → Forum → Thread trails.
4. If a page needs a special trail (e.g. admin area), extend the shared component via props instead of copy-pasting markup.
5. ESLint rule `no-manual-breadcrumb` will be introduced; temporary exceptions must be commented `// TODO: use <Breadcrumbs>`.

## Migration Plan
- Replace stubbed breadcrumb implementations in:
  • `client/src/pages/forums/[forum_slug].tsx`
  • `client/src/pages/threads/[thread_slug].tsx`
  • `client/src/pages/zones/[slug].tsx`
- Create `Breadcrumbs` component under `components/common` that wraps `@/components/ui/breadcrumb` primitives.

## Success Indicators
- Zero occurrences of `BreadcrumbPage>` hard-coded outside the shared component.
- Navigation updates automatically when forum/zone names change in config.
